{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"dkdtvct3q6f8lggmoqrqf43","title":"Collection Framework","desc":"","updated":1717342998926,"created":1713633121566,"custom":{},"fname":"lang.java.lib.collection","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"cs"},"contentHash":"14f1c0feb7912b01dddf43d4d4d71c2e","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.collection","id":"dkdtvct3q6f8lggmoqrqf43","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"data.structure","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":130,"offset":130},"end":{"line":2,"column":148,"offset":148},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"data.structure"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.collection","id":"dkdtvct3q6f8lggmoqrqf43","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"lang.java.lib.interfaces.marker.serializable","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":36,"offset":374},"end":{"line":8,"column":84,"offset":422},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.interfaces.marker.serializable"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.collection","id":"dkdtvct3q6f8lggmoqrqf43","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"lang.java.lib.interfaces.marker.cloneable","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":89,"offset":427},"end":{"line":8,"column":134,"offset":472},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.interfaces.marker.cloneable"}}],"anchors":{"references":{"type":"header","text":"References","value":"references","line":25,"column":1,"depth":2}},"children":["fi3xznhjsf8ezkolih7torp","atl12pgb3ce7dsbhcun9uws","rpb0p7ld8g30mdscf1r32re","bsk6mro2a2qy52s1c3jkvqu","e3yh106bjbj4yim4rsaulv6","b17y2tutvawdczru2nczk98","1a4jvgqvofjnpwiju5bq0pt"],"parent":"9zir47v5yk3jbddsjyqkt53","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"collection-framework\">Collection Framework<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#collection-framework\"></a></h1>\n<p>Java Collection Framework defines several classes and interfaces to represent group of individual objects as single entity, i.e. <a href=\"/cs/notes/5rqq4ui5cu6wak3k7p7ebb8\">Data Structures</a>.  </p>\n<p>Although, referred to as a framework, it functions more like a library with a collection of classes and interfaces.</p>\n<p>💡 Every Collection class is based on some standard data structure.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>All Collection Classes implement <a href=\"/cs/notes/mbwwjk3x17fjagziw7d0ky6\">Serializable</a> and <a href=\"/cs/notes/6fe2bcmqj3rdsd3wd82k3lp\">Cloneable</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Why though?</p>\n<p>  Collections <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>≡</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\equiv</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4637em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≡</span></span></span></span></span> Containers in C++ → used to transfer</p>\n<p>  To transfer object from one place to another, it should be <strong>serializable</strong>.</p>\n<p>  When sent from one place to another, the receiver makes a copy of it and operates on it → <strong>clonable</strong></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"references\">References<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#references\"></a></h2>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/collections/overview.html#:~:text=Not%2C%20strictly%20speaking%2C%20a%20part%20of%20the%20collections,and%20relies%20on%20some%20of%20the%20same%20infrastructure.\">Collections Framework Overview - Java - Oracle Documentation</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/cs/notes/fi3xznhjsf8ezkolih7torp\">Collection Frameworks Cheatsheet</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/cs/notes/rpb0p7ld8g30mdscf1r32re\">Collection Interface</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/cs/notes/e3yh106bjbj4yim4rsaulv6\">Collections Class</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/cs/notes/atl12pgb3ce7dsbhcun9uws\">Dictionary</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/cs/notes/bsk6mro2a2qy52s1c3jkvqu\">Map</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","title":"Computer Science","desc":"","updated":1715103618849,"created":1713296516553,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"cs"},"contentHash":"36faf26c6be438d4aed355d72b55a110","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"arch","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":3,"offset":105},"end":{"line":6,"column":11,"offset":113},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"arch"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"paradigm","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":3,"offset":159},"end":{"line":11,"column":15,"offset":171},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"paradigm"}}],"anchors":{"references":{"type":"header","text":"References","value":"references","line":23,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["0xgibr34qhbv1edksyoxakk","t246wcci6dy9lnof7l1os4l","71sipcgr0pdqyxnmntvx28w","6k8qk8m6zofpfla0wr8eajn","szmkrtr9ezx1kg3mzcamb7m","a6m88ijp6ij9aam2ose0k6j","7t5m5bvvkqqmexze4ymednf","4bgqfqpix52j5ek9oawj3lw","ng2w78j1rxy1prvsi6zc9j3","q1uj4uy5892ahhlgrn1wi7m","qnetoavqu273jl4iovqtk76","qanoka2zolegyqtrlis4sg2","nsbtaj4zu6fmgjuooy55mbx","uc1prffatcsbivlbj2yud2i","azqmz08s69usdskj1a7v94c","v3e3a8biac8damddtjrn7az","qqb74o6z75mxkm5ygg7d6h2"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\n\nThese notes are arranged into the below topics:\n\n- AI (Sorry this is on the top, list is alphabetic)\n- [[arch]]\n- Data\n- Execution\n- Languages\n- Semantics\n- [[paradigm]]\n- Philosophy\n- Dev\n- Tools\n- Type Theory\n\n## References\n\n- Hierarchy inpiration - [Map of Computer Science](https://www.flickr.com/photos/95869671@N08/36231833334/in/photostream/lightbox/)"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadCon